% Automatisch generiert — Thema: Marijuana Legalization
% arg/1 Fakten
arg(pro82).  % [pro] But with legalization, proper means to settle disputes would be created.
arg(pro15).  % [pro] 27% of supporters say legalization would lead to improved regulation of marijuana.
arg(pro15b).  % [pro] 27% of supporters say legalization would lead to increased tax revenues.
arg(pro4).  % [pro] The paper of record argues that cannabis prohibition creates social costs, supporting legalization.
arg(pro4b).  % [pro] The paper of record argues that cannabis prohibition has a racist history, supporting legalization.
arg(pro4c).  % [pro] The paper of record argues that cannabis prohibition wastes resources, supporting legalization.
arg(pro95).  % [pro] Marijuana also helps medical conditions as a more natural substitute to pharmaceuticals.
arg(pro36).  % [pro] Teen marijuana use has fallen slightly over the past five years.
arg(pro36b).  % [pro] Four states and the District of Columbia have legalized marijuana, and 23 other states allow medical use.
arg(pro32).  % [pro] Though more adults are smoking pot, the MTF data suggests that teens aren't following suit.
arg(pro29).  % [pro] People believe that legalizing recreational weed will cut off a revenue stream for illegal drug traders.
arg(con18).  % [con] There is a good reason why most habitual marijuana users come off as stupid.
arg(con95).  % [con] The study found that even those who quit in adulthood were not able to recover the IQ points.
arg(con14).  % [con] Any time marijuana use is made legal, drug accessibility to children will increase.
arg(con87).  % [con] Marijuana tends to be a starter drug for people who move on to heavier duty drugs, whether those drugs are legal or illegal.
arg(con87b).  % [con] I do not think that having marijuana as a starter drug is something we want for our society.
arg(con87c).  % [con] Society is changing rapidly to a different type of society, and nobody is getting a chance to discuss marijuana legalization.
arg(con115).  % [con] According to social worker Shannon McPherson, marijuana legalization has been bad for the whole Pueblo community.
arg(con70).  % [con] Marijuana is even more toxic than cigarette smoke.
arg(con12).  % [con] Marijuana is terrible for your physical health.

% att/2 Fakten  (Dung 1995 — binär; Typ/conf aus LLM-Kandidaten als Kommentar)
att(con14, pro15).  % [NONE] conf=75 — Con14 asserts that legalization increases child accessibility, undermining pro15's premise that legalization improves regulation.
att(con115, pro15).  % [NONE] conf=70 — The assertion that legalization has been bad for a community challenges the positive outcome (improved regulation) claimed by the pro argument.
att(con115, pro15b).  % [NONE] conf=70 — B claims overall community harm, undermining A's positive tax‑revenue implication
