att(con12, pro15b).  % [NONE] conf=80 — B highlights severe health risks, contradicting A's favorable economic claim
att(con18, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=75 — B attacks the notion that prohibition is harmful by portraying users negatively
att(con95, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=75 — B presents evidence of lasting IQ loss, challenging A's claim that prohibition creates social costs
att(con115, pro4b).  % [NONE] conf=85 — B claims legalization harms a community, directly opposing A's conclusion that legalization is justified.
