att(con14, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=70 — con14 claims legalization raises child access, contradicting pro4’s conclusion that legalization is beneficial.
att(con87, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=80 — con87 asserts a gateway effect, challenging the desirability of legalization advocated by pro4.
att(con87b, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=75 — con87b opposes marijuana as a starter drug, undermining pro4’s support for legalization.
att(con115, pro4).  % [NONE] conf=70 — con115 cites negative community impact of legalization, countering pro4’s pro‑legalization stance.
att(con12, pro4b).  % [NONE] conf=80 — B claims health harms, challenging the desirability of legalization advocated by A
att(con18, pro4c).  % [NONE] conf=70 — B attacks the desirability of legalization by portraying users negatively
att(con95, pro4c).  % [NONE] conf=75 — B presents evidence of lasting IQ loss, undermining A’s pro‑legalization stance
att(con14, pro4c).  % [NONE] conf=80 — B argues legalization increases child access, contradicting A’s conclusion
att(con87, pro4c).  % [NONE] conf=80 — B claims marijuana is a gateway drug, challenging A’s argument for legalization
